A 100 level Chemical Engineering student of the University of Port Harcourt, Hilkmat Gbadamosi was said to have committed suicide on Saturday. She was said to have battled with a terminal illness. A source said the deceased was depressed by the pains of the alleged illness and decided to poison herself. Another source said took her life because she was jilted by her boyfriend. Her body was said to have been found in her room by the caretaker of her rented apartment. The spokesman of the institution, William Wodi, said he was yet to be briefed about incident. But the spokesman of the state police command, Nnamdi Omoni, confirmed the incident. JUST IN: Uniport student commits suicide JSS 3 girl commits  suicide over  love affair Final year varsity student dies in hotel